The paper deals with a data structure problem related to trees and strings, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category. The problem is related to weighted trees, which could also place it in the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) category. The paper also mentions a periodicity-based insight, which could suggest a connection to the cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) category. The application of the problem to suffix trees could suggest a connection to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) category. Finally, the paper uses several data structure tools, which could suggest a connection to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) category.
